If there is something to say about Cebu Bar & Bistro that hasn't been said online before, perhaps it's only THIS:  They are among the TOP of a VERY short list of old school, gracious, know-your name & shake your hand/ hug you (pre-social distancing!!!) stop by the table & say hello proprietors, Bartenders & Servers. The Service industry is BUILT on certain ideals & they personally SHINE light into all of them.  They've got extraordinary Ambiance (EVEN WHEN HAVING TO DO IT ALL OUTDOORS!!!) Their carefully constructed, gorgeously designed "cabanas" are individually heated, lighted, curated with no expense spared... Their food is exceptional (thanks to Chef  Carlos Rodríguez-Lima !!!) greedier servers knowledgeable &  Mixologists talented, BUT, most importantly, L❤ve & warmth radiates from each.  Brooklyn is so lucky to have a Cebu Bar & Bistro... to call Ted Fleetwood Nugent &  Michael Esposito Ambassadors of our town & that delectable FOOD, damn, yo... Go get you some Cebu, everybody. You will be so glad you did!!!!!!!!  (You're clearly a regular when your accessories are coordinated with Bay Ridge, Brooklyn 's wonderful Cebu Bar & Bistro's chairs !!!)

First off let me start by saying I don’t usually leave reviews,I’m not a complainer whatsoever,BUT after having tried to meet a dear  friend this evening to enjoy a post New Year’s dinner I was beyond disappointed.It was bitterly cold and from the looks of it it seems like an nice outdoor set up except for the fact that the heat lamps are so puny and do absolutely nothing to keep you warm unless of course you were the guy at the table next to us who had a nice large lamp practically glued to his face because apparently he reserved it.So terribly uncomfortable to have to try and eat this way. The entire make shift shed is completely open and let’s all the cold air and wind in, next we ordered soups and truffle fries,all of which were tasty for the most part until of course they were ice cold in about 5 minutes flat due the the lousy set up and temps, we were so cold we had to get the check early and leave abruptly,but now for the grand finale..the check was so over the top price wise we were completely disgusted. Twelve dollars for a French onion soup ?? Come on Cebu, your in Bay Ridge for crying out loud, and drinks $15-??So to sum it up ,bad set up and overpriced,I am NEVER going back,I wld have been happier to spend the same money elsewhere on the avenue and  would have been warm and had a nice full meal. It’s a thumbs way down for me ,get your act together Cebu!

I had a similar experience as the previous reviewer Stephanie  I called to make a reservation for a first time dining at this place but no one was answering so I went there and was told there is a 2 hr wait. Fair enough since it is a Friday night. The manager though did not seem too interested in being accommodating or informative. Just told me to call to make a reservation and ignored me on 08/14/20 when I told him no one is answering the phone. I tried calling the next day and after a few tries, a young lady finally picked up and told me only walk ins-no reservations. I was floored. This place doesn’t seem customer friendly at all. My husband asked me why am I bothering at this point. I’m glad they let me know that this is not a place I want to give my money to.

Been going here for years and was disappointed today. I sat at a table for two and decided to move my chair because it was placed on an incline on the sidewalk causing the seating to be uneven. Not too long after that the manager approached me and asked me to move my seat back to where it originally was due to distance requirements from Coronavirus. I have no issue with this but the table directly behind me was not occupied and I mentioned this and was still told I needed to move the seat back to where it was. Mind you the tables were not even six feet apart so my seating either way was not technically in accordance with regulations. I moved it back with no fuss because I was trying to enjoy a Saturday afternoon with my daughter. Eventually a couple did come and sit at that table and moved their seat in such a way that I was told I couldn't. Then the table behind where my daughter was sitting became fully occupied with five people and they moved their seat in such a way that I was told was not allowed. I said nothing and ate my food which mind you was not good. My daughter ordered a linguine with garlic and oil sauce that had no garlic in it and the rapini was soggy mush. My salad was okay however it had a little bit too much dressing but that really wasn't the issue. The food was definitely overrated and not up to par. The manager walked by the seating area twice while I was eating and didn't bother to say anything to the other people so it annoyed me that I was targeted when those tables were empty. The reason for this negative review is because this manager had the audacity to say something to me in a very sarcastic tone apologizing for asking me to move my seat. I wish he didn't say anything because I felt the need to let him know other people were doing what they wanted with this seating and he said nothing to them and this resulted in an unpleasant exchange on my Saturday afternoon for a salad and a bowl of pasta that ended up costing me $75. I will not be going back here and I've been going here for years and years and years...

If I could give it less than one star I would. I went there last Monday with a group of 8 girls. When three of us arrived early, they showed us to our seats. They didn’t even bring over water, bread or anything. They didn’t ask if we wanted a drink. After 1/2 hour someone finally came over we asked if we could order drinks. We all gave him our order to which he responded , wait let me go get your waitress. Another 10 minutes later, our waitress finally came over and took our drink menu. Then we ordered food which took forever to come. In addition they brought us a regular menu and an iPad menu; both menus had the same items. From what I remember the menu at Cebu was a book and pages long. This was a menu of maybe 20 items.  There was no variety and the portions were incredibly small. Not enough food at all. We noticed a menu up on the wall and when I asked how many lobster ravioli came in an order the waitress replied with “oh that’s our in memory menu, we no longer serve those things. Those were on the menu years ago”. From this we were extremely disappointed and decided to get the check and leave. 5 drinks, 4 appetizers and a $300 plus bill later- ridiculous! When it was time to get our keys for our cars- we wanted to leave them in the parked spots because we needed to go elsewhere to eat; the valet guy had no idea where our cars were parked and when he finally realized he said he had to move one because it was parked illegally. It’s such a shame. I remember loving Cebu and it’s menu. I will never go again.

Cebu is one of our go-to spots for special occasions and last night they exemplified why.  They were having a rough night, service was slow, and they had a couple of missteps.  For many other restaurants, it would have been a bad experience.  Instead, Cebu really stepped it up and while they couldn't control the timing, they made an incredible effort to make things right for us and, from what we could overhear, for the other patrons as well.  You really learn more about a place when things are going wrong than when everything runs as it does normally.  Cebu really demonstrated why they're worth trusting with a special event.  No matter what, they're going to make sure you have a great time.  And of course, the food was phenomenal, as always!
